# =============================================================================
# Repo hygiene for the public conference release.
#
# The project's REPRODUCIBILITY policy — which data/ and results/ are committed
# on purpose (frozen prompts, generations, raw judgments, tables, figures) —
# lives in mirror-test-llms/.gitignore and is intentionally kept. This root
# file only strips clutter, local state, and heavy duplicates from the release.
# =============================================================================

# Per-session working snapshots — each Output/SessionN is a full copy of the
# repo from a past run; huge and redundant for a code release.
Output/
*.zip

# Local agent / editor / OS state (never part of the release)
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Transient orchestrator bookkeeping (regenerated on every run; not a source)
orchestrator_state.json

# Stray junk
New Text Document.txt
*.tmp

# Heavy rendered PDF duplicate of the protocol; the text source of truth that
# the code's "protocol §N" references point to is mirrortest.md (kept).
mirror_test_llms_research_protocol.md.pdf

# Root-level convenience copies of the runner notebooks. The canonical, versioned
# copies live under mirror-test-llms/ ; these root copies are auto-regenerated by
# tools/build_kaggle_notebook.py and tools/build_extension_notebook.py.
/kaggle_run_all.ipynb
/kaggle_extend_families.ipynb

# Python / notebook / cache noise (belt-and-suspenders across the whole tree)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.cache/
hf_cache/
.venv/
venv/
